cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this codebase, please cite both the software and the associated paper."
type: software
title: "Granularity-Aligned Metacognition for LLMs"
abstract: >
  A research codebase investigating metacognitive monitoring for LLMs.
  Core contributions: (1) Boundary-Local Amplification — feedback retry
  produces an inverted-U benefit pattern concentrated in the near-boundary
  zone (p = 0.0008); (2) The Granularity Alignment Principle — a signal's
  predictive power depends on whether its measurement granularity matches
  the decision granularity; (3) Capability Router — a benchmark system
  for studying accept/verify/escalate routing decisions.
